text: Catagela adjurella is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Francis Walker in 1863. It is found in Sri Lanka, India and China (Shandong, Henan, Jiangsu, Anhui, Zhejiang, Hubei, Hunan, Guangdong, Hainan, Yunnan). ==References== Category:Moths described in 1863 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Catagela adjurella
